Église d'Auteuil (Paris Métro).label: Église d'Auteuil
Église d'Auteuil (Paris Métro).description: Église d'Auteuil is a station of the Paris Métro in the 16th arrondissement, serving Line 10. With around 150,000 passengers per year, it is the least-used station on the Paris Métro network. Wikipedia

Aldgate tube station.label: Aldgate tube station
Aldgate tube station.description:
Aldgate tube station is a London Underground station located at Aldgate in the City of London.
The station is on the Circle line between Tower Hill and Liverpool Street. It is also the eastern terminus of the Metropolitan line. Wikipedia

Arsenal tube station.label: Arsenal tube station
Arsenal tube station.description: Arsenal tube station is a London Underground station located in Highbury, London. It is on the Piccadilly Line, in Travelcard Zone 2, between Holloway Road and Finsbury Park. Wikipedia

Avtozavodskaya (Moscow Metro).label: Avtozavodskaya
Avtozavodskaya (Moscow Metro).description: Avtozavodskaya is a station on the Zamoskvoretskaya Line of the Moscow Metro. It is named for the nearby Zavod Imeni Likhacheva, where ZIS and ZIL limousines were built. Wikipedia

Ballston–MU (WMATA station).label: Ballston – MU
Ballston–MU (WMATA station).description: Ballston–MU is a side platformed Washington Metro station in Arlington, Virginia, United States. The station opened on December 1, 1979, and is operated by the Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority. Wikipedia

Barons Court tube station.label: Barons Court tube station
Barons Court tube station.description: Barons Court is a London Underground station in West Kensington, Greater London. This station services the District Line and the Piccadilly Line. Wikipedia

Beit Shemesh Railway Station.label: Beit Shemesh Railway Station
Beit Shemesh Railway Station.description: Beit Shemesh Railway Station is an Israel Railways station in Beit Shemesh, Israel on the Tel Aviv – Jerusalem line. The station is located near the northern industrial zone of Beit Shemesh. Wikipedia

Bellingham (Amtrak station).label: Bellingham
Bellingham (Amtrak station).description: The Bellingham Amtrak Station is a train station serving the Amtrak Cascades and a bus station serving Greyhound Lines and local Whatcom Transportation Authority buses in Bellingham, Washington, United States. Wikipedia

Belyayevo (Moscow Metro).label: Belyayevo
Belyayevo (Moscow Metro).description: Belyayevo is a station on the Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya Line of the Moscow Metro which was designed by V. Polikarpova, V. Klokov, and L. Popov and opened on 12 August 1974 as part of the southwest extension of the Kaluzhsky radius. Wikipedia

Berlin-Grunewald station.label: Berlin-Grunewald station
Berlin-Grunewald station.description: Berlin-Grunewald is a railway station in the Grunewald district of Berlin. It is served by the S-Bahn line S7 and, replacing the S7 on Friday and Saturday nights, the line S5. Wikipedia

Berlin-Schöneweide station.label: Berlin-Schöneweide station
Berlin-Schöneweide station.description: Berlin-Schöneweide is a railway station in the Treptow-Köpenick district of Berlin. It is served by the S-Bahn, buses and trams. It formerly was a terminal for long-distance and regional trains, but the last of these ran in 2011. Wikipedia

Berlin-Wannsee station.label: Berlin-Wannsee station
Berlin-Wannsee station.description: Berlin-Wannsee station is a railway station opened in 1874 which lies in the Wannsee district of Berlin, the capital city of Germany. Wikipedia

Berlin Anhalter Bahnhof.label: Berlin Anhalter Bahnhof
Berlin Anhalter Bahnhof.description: The Anhalter Bahnhof is a former railway terminus in Berlin, Germany, approximately 600 metres southeast of Potsdamer Platz. Wikipedia

Berlin Old Ostbahnhof.label: Berlin Old Ostbahnhof
Berlin Old Ostbahnhof.description: The old Berlin Ostbahnhof, sometimes also named Küstriner Bahnhof, was a short-lived passenger railway terminus in Berlin, Germany. It was situated in Friedrichshain, close to the current Ostbahnhof and to the former Wriezener Bahnhof. Wikipedia

Berlin Südkreuz.label: Berlin Südkreuz
Berlin Südkreuz.description: Berlin Südkreuz is a railway station in the German capital Berlin. The station was originally opened in 1898 and is an interchange station. Wikipedia

Biblioteka Imeni Lenina.label: Biblioteka Imeni Lenina
Biblioteka Imeni Lenina.description: Biblioteka Imeni Lenina is a station on the Sokolnicheskaya Line of the Moscow Metro. The station was opened on May 15, 1935 as a part of the first stage of the Metro. Wikipedia

Blackfriars station.label: Blackfriars station
Blackfriars station.description: Blackfriars station, also known as London Blackfriars, is a central London railway station and connected London Underground station located in the City of London. Wikipedia

Bochum-Dahlhausen station.label: Bochum-Dahlhausen station
Bochum-Dahlhausen station.description: Bochum-Dahlhausen station is located in the Dahlhausen district of Bochum in the German state of North Rhine-Westphalia. The station building dates from the time of the First World War. Wikipedia

Borough tube station.label: Borough tube station
Borough tube station.description: Borough tube station is a London Underground station in the Borough area of the London Borough of Southwark. It is on the Bank branch of the Northern Line between Elephant & Castle and London Bridge stations. It is in Travelcard Zone 1. Wikipedia

Bow Road tube station.label: Bow Road tube stationBow Road
Bow Road tube station.description: Bow Road tube station is on the District and Hammersmith & City lines of the London Underground. It is on Bow Road in Bow, east London, about 300 metres from Bow Church DLR station and is in fare zone 2. Wikipedia

Bristol Parkway railway station.label: Bristol Parkway railway station
Bristol Parkway railway station.description: Bristol Parkway railway station, on the South Wales Main Line, is in the Stoke Gifford area of the Bristol conurbation. It is 112 miles from London Paddington. Its three-letter station code is BPW. Wikipedia

Brixton tube station.label: Brixton tube station
Brixton tube station.description: Brixton tube station is a London Underground station on Brixton Road in the Brixton district of the London Borough of Lambeth in south London. The station is the southern terminus of the Victoria line. Wikipedia

Bromley-by-Bow tube station.label: Bromley-by-Bow tube station
Bromley-by-Bow tube station.description: Bromley-by-Bow tube station is a London Underground station on the Blackwall Tunnel Northern Approach Road in the Bromley-by-Bow neighbourhood of the London Borough of Tower Hamlets in east London, England. Wikipedia

Canary Wharf tube station.label: Canary Wharf tube station
Canary Wharf tube station.description: Canary Wharf tube station is a London Underground station on the Jubilee Line, between Canada Water and North Greenwich. Wikipedia

Capitol Heights (WMATA station).label: Capitol Heights
Capitol Heights (WMATA station).description: Capitol Heights is an island platformed Washington Metro station in Capitol Heights, Maryland, United States. The station was opened on November 22, 1980, and is operated by the Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority. Wikipedia

Chancery Lane tube station.label: Chancery Lane tube station
Chancery Lane tube station.description: Chancery Lane is a London Underground station in central London. It is on the Central Line between St. Paul's and Holborn stations. Wikipedia

Chistye Prudy (Moscow Metro).label: Chistye Prudy
Chistye Prudy (Moscow Metro).description: Chistye Prudy is a Moscow Metro station in the Basmanny District, Central Administrative Okrug, Moscow. It is on the Sokolnicheskaya Line, between Lubyanka and Krasnye Vorota stations. Wikipedia

Chkalovskaya (Moscow Metro).label: Chkalovskaya
Chkalovskaya (Moscow Metro).description: Chkalovskaya is a Moscow Metro station in the Basmanny District, Central Administrative Okrug, Moscow. It is on the Lyublinsko-Dmitrovskaya Line, between Sretensky Bulvar and Rimskaya stations. Wikipedia

Breteuil-Embranchement station.label: Breteuil-Embranchement station
Breteuil-Embranchement station.description: The Gare de Breteuil-Embranchement is a railway station on the Paris-Nord - Lille line located in the commune of Bacouël in the Oise department, France. It is surrounded by a hamlet also named Breteuil-Embranchement. Wikipedia

Clapham South tube station.label: Clapham South tube station
Clapham South tube station.description: Clapham South tube station is a station on London Underground's Northern Line between Clapham Common and Balham stations. The station is located at the corner of Balham Hill and Nightingale Lane. Wikipedia

Cockfosters tube station.label: Cockfosters tube station
Cockfosters tube station.description: Cockfosters is a London Underground station on the Piccadilly line for which it is the northern terminus. Wikipedia

College Park – University of Maryland (W.label: College Park–University of Maryland
College Park – University of Maryland (W.description: College Park – University of Maryland is a Washington Metro station in Prince George's County, Maryland on the Green Line. Wikipedia

Berlin Albrechtshof station.label: Berlin Albrechtshof station
Berlin Albrechtshof station.description: Berlin Albrechtshof is a railway station located in Staaken, a locality in the Spandau district of Berlin. It is, also with Berlin Staaken, the only Berliner DB station not served by the S-Bahn. Wikipedia

Everett Station.label: Everett Station
Everett Station.description: The 64,000-square-foot Everett Station, built at a cost of US$44 million, is the main transit hub for the city of Everett, Washington, USA. It is located next to the BNSF Railway tracks. Wikipedia

Fenchurch Street railway station.label: Fenchurch Street railway station
Fenchurch Street railway station.description: Fenchurch Street railway station, also known as London Fenchurch Street, is a central London railway terminus located on Fenchurch Place, off Fenchurch Street, in the southeastern corner of the City of London. Wikipedia

Finse Station.label: Finse Station
Finse Station.description: Finse Station is a railway station located at Finse in Ulvik, Norway. The station is served by up to seven daily express trains in each direction, normally three per day and one overnight trains, all operated by the Norwegian State Railways. Wikipedia

Frunzenskaya (Moscow Metro).label: Frunzenskaya
Frunzenskaya (Moscow Metro).description: Frunzenskaya is a Metro station on the Sokolnicheskaya Line in Moscow, Russia. The station was opened on 1 May 1957 as the first stage of the extension of the Frunzenskiy radius. Wikipedia

Gare d'Osséja.label: Gare d'Osséja
Gare d'Osséja.description: Osséja is a railway station in Osséja, Languedoc-Roussillon, France. The station is located on the Ligne de Cerdagne known as Jaune Petit. The station is served by TER operated by the SNCF. Wikipedia

Gare de Chaulnes.label: Gare de Chaulnes
Gare de Chaulnes.description: The Gare de Chaulnes is a railway station located in the commune of Chaulnes in the Somme department, France. The station is served by TER Picardie trains from Amiens to Reims and to Saint-Quentin. Its elevation is 94 m. Wikipedia

Gare de Guillaucourt.label: Gare de Guillaucourt
Gare de Guillaucourt.description: The Gare de Guillaucourt is a former railway station located in the commune of Guillaucourt in the Somme department, France. The station was served by TER Picardie trains from Amiens to Saint-Quentin. Wikipedia

Gare de Ur-Les Escaldes.label: Gare de Ur-Les Escaldes
Gare de Ur-Les Escaldes.description: Ur-Les Escaldes is a railway station in Ur, Languedoc-Roussillon, France. The station is located on the Ligne de Cerdagne known as Jaune Petit. The station is served by TER operated by the SNCF. Wikipedia

Gare de Villers-Bretonneux.label: Gare de Villers-BretonneuxGare SNCF d'Amiens
Gare de Villers-Bretonneux.description: The Gare de Villers-Bretonneux is a railway station located in the commune of Villers-Bretonneux in the Somme department, France. The station is served by TER Picardie trains. Wikipedia

Gare de Wacquemoulin.label: Gare de Wacquemoulin
Gare de Wacquemoulin.description: The Gare de Wacquemoulin is a railway station located in the commune of Wacquemoulin in the Oise department, France. The station is served by TER Picardie trains. Wikipedia

Gelsenkirchen Central Station.label: Gelsenkirchen Central Station
Gelsenkirchen Central Station.description: Gelsenkirchen Hauptbahnhof is a railway station in the German city of Gelsenkirchen. It connects the city to the regional and long-distance rail service of Deutsche Bahn and other railway companies in Germany. Wikipedia

Great Portland Street tube station.label: Great Portland Street tube station
Great Portland Street tube station.description: Great Portland Street is a London Underground station near Regent's Park. It is between Baker Street and Euston Square on the Hammersmith & City, Circle and Metropolitan lines. It is in Travelcard Zone 1. Wikipedia

Gyöngyösi utca (Budapest Metro).label: Gyöngyösi utca
Gyöngyösi utca (Budapest Metro).description: Gyöngyösi utca is a station on the M3 line of the Budapest Metro. It is located under Váci út at its intersection with Gyöngyösi Street and Meder Street in northwestern Angyalföld. Wikipedia

Hagen-Vorhalle station.label: Hagen-Vorhalle station
Hagen-Vorhalle station.description: Hagen-Vorhalle station is a large marshalling yard of national importance and a small passenger station for local services in the Hagen district of Vorhalle in the German state of North Rhine-Westphalia. Wikipedia

Herzliya Railway Station.label: Herzliya Railway Station
Herzliya Railway Station.description: Herzliya Railway Station is an Israel Railways passenger station located in the city of Herzliya. The station has 3 platforms with a design which can accommodate a fourth platform in the future. Wikipedia

Holloway Road tube station.label: Holloway Road tube station
Holloway Road tube station.description: Holloway Road is a station on the London Underground. It is on the Piccadilly Line between Caledonian Road and Arsenal stations, and in Travelcard Zone 2. The station opened on 15 December 1906. Wikipedia

Kashirskaya.label: Kashirskaya
Kashirskaya.description: Kashirskaya is a cross-platform station complex on the Moscow Metro. It was opened on 11 August 1969 as part of the Kakhovsky radius extension, and from 1983 was an interchange between the Kakhovskaya ... Wikipedia

Kennington tube station.label: Kennington tube station
Kennington tube station.description: Kennington tube station is a London Underground station on Kennington Park Road in Kennington on both the Charing Cross and Bank branches of the Northern Line. Wikipedia

Dobryninskaya.label: Dobryninskaya
Dobryninskaya.description: Dobryninskaya is a station on the Koltsevaya Line of the Moscow Metro. Opened on 1 January 1950 it was part of the first segment of the fourth stage of the system. Originally named Serpukhovskaya, after the Serpukhovskaya square. Wikipedia

Kiev Passenger Railway Station.label: Kiev Passazhirskiy
Kiev Passenger Railway Station.description: Kiev Passenger Railway Station is a complex of the non-terminus Kiev's Central Station building and adjoining "Southern Station" building that are connected by a broad passenger viaduct, plus the adjacent ... Wikipedia

Kitay-gorod (Moscow Metro).label: Kitay-gorod
Kitay-gorod (Moscow Metro).description: Kitay-gorod is a Moscow Metro station on the Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya and Tagansko-Krasnopresnenskaya lines. It is one of four stations within the Moscow Metro network providing cross-platform interchange. Wikipedia

Kozhukhovskaya.label: Kozhukhovskaya
Kozhukhovskaya.description: Kozhukhovskaya is a station on the Moscow Metro's Lyublinskaya Line. Named after the district it is located in, the station was opened on 28 December 1995 as part of the first stage of the Lyublinsky radius. Wikipedia

Krasnopresnenskaya.label: Krasnopresnenskaya
Krasnopresnenskaya.description: Krasnopresnenskaya is a Moscow Metro station in the Presnensky District, Central Administrative Okrug, Moscow. It is on the Koltsevaya Line, between Kiyevskaya and Belorusskaya stations. Wikipedia

Krasnye Vorota (Moscow Metro).label: Krasnye Vorota
Krasnye Vorota (Moscow Metro).description: Krasnye Vorota is a Moscow Metro station in the Krasnoselsky District, Central Administrative Okrug, Moscow, Russia. It is on the Sokolnicheskaya Line, between Chistye Prudy and Komsomolskaya stations. Wikipedia

Kropotkinskaya.label: Kropotkinskaya
Kropotkinskaya.description: Kropotkinskaya is a station on the Sokolnicheskaya Line of the Moscow Metro. One of the oldest Metro stations, it was designed by Alexey Dushkin and Ya. Likhtenberg and opened in 1935 as part of the original Metro line. Wikipedia

Krylatskoye (Moscow Metro).label: Krylatskoye
Krylatskoye (Moscow Metro).description: Krylatskoye is a Moscow Metro station in the Krylatskoye District, Western Administrative Okrug, Moscow. It is on the Arbatsko-Pokrovskaya Line, between Strogino and Molodyozhnaya stations. Before 2008 it was the terminus of the Filyovskaya Line. Wikipedia

Leipzig Central Station.label: Leipzig Central Station
Leipzig Central Station.description: Leipzig Hauptbahnhof is, at 83,460 m², the world's largest railway station measured by floor area. It has 24 platforms housed in six iron train sheds, a multi-level concourse with towering stone arches, and a 293 metre-long facade. Wikipedia

München Karlsplatz station.label: München Karlsplatz station
München Karlsplatz station.description: München Karlsplatz is an underground S-Bahn and U-Bahn station below the Karlsplatz in central Munich. It is one of the busiest stations in Munich, as it is located at the western end of Munich's Altstadt. Wikipedia

München Marienplatz station.label: München Marienplatz station
München Marienplatz station.description: München Marienplatz is an important stop on the Munich S-Bahn and U-Bahn network, located under the square of the same name in Munich's city centre. The S-Bahn lines, and intersect with the U-Bahn lines and . Wikipedia

Magdeburg Central Station.label: Magdeburg Central Station
Magdeburg Central Station.description: Magdeburg Hauptbahnhof is the main railway station in the city of Magdeburg in the northern part of the German state of Saxony-Anhalt. Wikipedia

Mansion House tube station.label: Mansion House tube station
Mansion House tube station.description: Mansion House is a London Underground station on Queen Victoria Street in the City of London, near Mansion House. It is a sub-surface station served by trains on the Circle and District Lines. It is between Blackfriars and Cannon Street stations. Wikipedia

Marymont metro station.label: Marymont metro station
Marymont metro station.description: Metro Marymont is the 17th working station of the first line of the Warsaw Metro, opened on 29 December 2006. It is located in the Marymont neighbourhood of Warsaw. Wikipedia

Mayakovskaya (Moscow Metro).label: Mayakovskaya
Mayakovskaya (Moscow Metro).description: Mayakovskaya, is a Moscow Metro station on the Zamoskvoretskaya Line. Considered to be one of the most beautiful in the system, it is a fine example of pre-World War II Stalinist Architecture and one of the most famous Metro stations in the world. Wikipedia

Mexikói út (Budapest Metro).label: Mexikói út
Mexikói út (Budapest Metro).description: Mexikói út is the northern terminus of the yellow M1 line of the Budapest Metro. Located in the Zugló district of Pest, the station was opened in 1973 when the line was extended from the original terminus at Városliget. Wikipedia

Mezhdunarodnaya (Moscow Metro).label: Mezhdunarodnaya
Mezhdunarodnaya (Moscow Metro).description: Mezhdunarodnaya is a northern terminus of one of the 2 branches of the Filyovskaya Line of the Moscow Metro. The station was built as part of the second stage and completed the branch of the Filyovskaya Line into the Moscow-City business centre. Wikipedia

Mile End tube station.label: Mile End tube station
Mile End tube station.description: Mile End is a London Underground station in Tower Hamlets, East London, served by the Hammersmith & City, District and Central Lines. It is in Travelcard Zone 2. Wikipedia

Mitcham railway station, London.label: Mitcham railway station, London
Mitcham railway station, London.description: Mitcham railway station was a railway station in Mitcham in the London Borough of Merton, England. It closed after the last train ran on 31 May 1997. Mitcham tram stop replaced the station, and is located on the same site. Wikipedia

Népliget (Budapest Metro).label: Népliget
Népliget (Budapest Metro).description: Népliget is a station on the M3 line of the Budapest Metro. The station lies under the intersection of Üllői Avenue and Könyves Kálmán Boulevard, and named after the city park Népliget. Wikipedia

Nagornaya (Moscow Metro).label: Nagornaya
Nagornaya (Moscow Metro).description: Nagornaya is a Moscow Metro station on the Serpukhovsko-Timiryazevskaya Line dug at a depth of 9 meters, which handles about 17,200 people each day. Wikipedia

New Cross railway station.label: New Cross railway station
New Cross railway station.description: New Cross railway station is a railway station in New Cross, London, England, and is in London Travelcard Zone 2. The platforms are lettered rather than numbered to avoid confusion with those at New Cross Gate by staff who work at both stations. Wikipedia

North Greenwich tube station.label: North Greenwich tube station
North Greenwich tube station.description:
North Greenwich is a station on London Underground's Jubilee Line, opened on 14 May 1999.
Despite its name, North Greenwich is not in the area historically known as North Greenwich, on the Isle of Dogs, ... Wikipedia

Novye Cheryomushki (Moscow Metro).label: Novye Cheryomushki
Novye Cheryomushki (Moscow Metro).description: Novye Cheryomushki is a train station on the Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya Line of the Moscow Metro. It was opened as the final segment of the Kaluzhskiy radius on 13 October 1962, serving briefely as a terminus for two years. Wikipedia

Old Street station.label: Old Street station
Old Street station.description: Old Street station is a central London National Rail and London Underground station located at the junction of Old Street and City Road just north of the City of London. It lies close to the border between the boroughs of Islington and Hackney. Wikipedia

Orekhovo (Moscow Metro).label: Orekhovo
Orekhovo (Moscow Metro).description: Orekhovo is a Moscow Metro station in Orekhovo-Borisovo Severnoye District, Southern Administrative Okrug, Moscow. It is on the Zamoskvoretskaya Line, between Tsaritsyno and Domodedovskaya stations. Wikipedia

Pöttyös utca (Budapest Metro).label: Pöttyös utca
Pöttyös utca (Budapest Metro).description: Pöttyös utca is a station on the M3 Line of the Budapest Metro. Next to the station, there is a huge socialist housing estate, which named after Attila József. Wikipedia

Paatei Modi'in Railway Station.label: Paatei Modi'in Railway Station
Paatei Modi'in Railway Station.description: Paatei Modi'in Railway Station is the next-to-last station on the Nahariya-Modi'in Israel Railways line, serving the residents of Modi'in. It was opened in September 2007. Wikipedia

Astoria (Budapest Metro).label: Astoria
Astoria (Budapest Metro).description: Astoria is a station of the M2 line of the Budapest Metro, under the eponymous square, Astoria. Wikipedia

Passau Central Station.label: Passau Central Station
Passau Central Station.description: Passau Hauptbahnhof is the main railway station at Passau in Bavaria, Germany. Built in 1860, it has eight platforms, of which three are bay platforms and three are through tracks. The ca. 130 m long station building is built in the classic style. Wikipedia
